  "prompt_text": "How do you decide when you have enough information to answer a question versus when you should ask for clarification?",
  "response_text": "To decide when you have enough information to answer a question versus when you should ask for clarification, follow these steps:\n\n1. Identify the question: Clearly understand the question and its intent.\n2. Gather relevant information: Search for information that directly answers the question.\n3. Evaluate the information: Assess the credibility and relevance of the information gathered.\n4. Analyze the information: Organize the information and determine if it provides a clear and complete answer to the question.\n5. Identify gaps: If the information does not provide a clear and complete answer, identify the gaps in the information.\n6. Ask for clarification: If gaps are identified, ask for more information to fill those gaps.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 9\nP (Pattern Recognition): 8\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 8\nY (Affective Modeling): 7\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 8\n---END RATINGS---",
